summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from S. L. Crawford and Clara M. Crawford, his wife, to the City of Seattle, dated the 7th day of November, 1908, to that portion of Lot 4, Block "E" Madrona Heights Addition to the City of Seattle, described as follow, to wit: Beginning at a point on the South line of said lot, said point being distant 65 feet east from the Southwest Corner of said lot; thence East along the South line thereof a distance of 77 feet to the S.E. corner of said lot; thence Northerly along the East line thereof to the Northeast corner of said lot; thence West along the North line thereof a distance of 109.4 feet to a point distant 30 feet East from the Northwest corner of said Lot; Thence southeasterly to the point of beginning.
